get.description: Return a specific instance of a collection. Isobaric is the only collection available. The date in current grib file is only instance available, format %Y%m%d%H0000, so string has to be 14 characters, where first 8 are a number and last 6 are all zeros, example 20240104000000. No data is returned, only info about the instance.

get.description:
Return data closest to a position.

This is the main function of this API. Needs a string with the coordinates, formated as a WKT. Example: POINT(11.9384 60.1699) or POINT(11 60).

schema.title: Coordinates, formated as a WKT point: POINT(11.9384 60.1699)
